================================================================================
PEPPER MAKES MINT BETTER

Installing Countertop Pepper
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. If the table you'd like to count is in a different database than the one
   containing your Mint records, you must specify it in:
   /countertop/db.php

2. Upload the /countertop/ directory and its contents to 
   /mint/pepper/brandonkelly/. If the directory /brandonkelly/ doesn't exist,
   create it.

3. Login to your Mint installation and in the Preferences click "Install" under
   Pepper.

4. Click the Countertop Pepper "Install" button. Click "Okay."

5. Specify the name of the table you'd like to count in the Preferences.

